(223, 'stuff', '(noun)', '/stʌf/', 'used to refer in a general way to things that people do, say, think, etc. / used to refer to a substance, material, group of objects, etc. when you do not know the name, when the name is not important or when it is obvious what you are talking about / đồ đạc', 'The chairs were covered in some sort of plastic stuff.\r\nThis hot sauce is good stuff.\r\nI don\'t know how you can eat that stuff!\r\nPeter\'s article had lots of interesting stuff in it.\r\nThere\'s still a lot of cool stuff happening in Manchester.\r\nI\'ve got loads of stuff to do today.', '', '', '2024-01-12 00:09:03', 'view/uploads/image/03_09_7_12_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/03_09_7_12_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
(224, 'go into', '(phrasal verb)', '', 'to start doing a particular type of work / to start an activity, or start to be in a particular state or condition / to discuss, describe, or explain something, esp. in a detailed or careful way', 'My son\'s planning to go into journalism.\r\nThe drug is still being tested and will not go into commercial production for at least two years.\r\nThis is the first book to go into her personal life as well as her work.', '', '', '2024-01-12 00:13:20', 'view/uploads/image/26_38_12_17_1_2024_image.png', '', '', 0),
