(228, 'equate', '(verb)', '/ɪˈkweɪt/', 'to consider one thing to be the same as or equal to another thing / to consider as the same, or to connect in your mind / to consider that one thing is the same as or similar to something else', 'He complained that there was a tendency to equate right-wing politics with self-interest.\r\nPeople sometimes equate money with happiness.\r\nFast cars are often equated with power and sex appeal.', '', '', '2024-01-12 01:01:28', 'view/uploads/image/51_56_17_12_1_2024_image.png', 'view/uploads/audio/28_01_8_12_1_2024_audio.mp3', '', 0),
